<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Simile" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Simile,</orth> a comparison (as a term of rhetoric): <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.1.45" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 1, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 5.2.54" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. V, 2, 54</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.2.89" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 2, 89</bibl> (Qq F<hi rend="sub">1</hi> <emph>smiles</emph>). <bibl n="shak. tro 3.2.183" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 2, 183</bibl>. <cit><quote>take all these --s to your command,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lc 227" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 227</bibl></cit> (i. e. symbolical love-tokens). In <bibl n="shak. aww 5.2.26" default="NO" valid="yes">All's V, 2, 26</bibl> some M. Edd. <emph>--s,</emph> O. Edd. <emph>smiles.</emph>
